"title": "6253: temptation, avoiding causing",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6253",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Any behaviour which might cause others to do wrong is to be avoided.</p>\n<h2>Warnings not to cause temptation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:1\">LUK 17:1</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Special care is needed to avoid tempting those whose faith is young</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:6\">MAT 18:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:42\">MRK 9:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:2\">LUK 17:2</a></p>\n<h2>Temptation is linked to passing judgment on others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:13\">ROM 14:13</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Allowance must be made to avoid causing temptation to those whose faith is weak</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:15\">ROM 14:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:21\">ROM 14:21</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Avoiding causing temptation by exercising Christian freedom responsibly</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:9-1Cor8:13\">1CO 8:9–8:13</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Examples of causing temptation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:1-Num25:2\">NUM 25:1–25:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:29\">PRO 16:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:15\">HAB 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:6\">MAT 18:6</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of restraining sin or temptation</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:21-Gen37:22\">GEN 37:21–37:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28-Acts20:31\">ACT 20:28–20:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:10-Eph6:13\">EPH 6:10–6:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:1-Heb12:3\">HEB 12:1–12:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:8-1Pet5:9\">1PE 5:8–5:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:7\">1JN 3:7</a></p>",
